{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/burns-scalds/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"a5e00295-b9af-5538-a258-cc901a71f289","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field ab772b1c-349f-4ec7-a7ab-a7f20187c6b4 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field ab772b1c-349f-4ec7-a7ab-a7f20187c6b4 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 6481740f-9444-4f3d-bec4-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field 2d1514d4-96bb-440a-851f-a7f20187c6b4 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 2d1514d4-96bb-440a-851f-a7f20187c6b4 --><!-- begin field 19d74373-bbba-4787-a49c-a7f20187c6b4 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 19d74373-bbba-4787-a49c-a7f20187c6b4 --><!-- begin field 21a915d2-4ea7-4bc8-b8b6-a7f20187c6b4 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 21a915d2-4ea7-4bc8-b8b6-a7f20187c6b4 --><!-- begin field 5f7f5483-1b8c-4c50-98ad-a7f20187c6b4 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 5f7f5483-1b8c-4c50-98ad-a7f20187c6b4 --><!-- begin field 43c29f69-9c21-413e-85b0-a7f20187c6b4 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 43c29f69-9c21-413e-85b0-a7f20187c6b4 --><!-- begin field 95aac697-5bbb-4a67-9486-a7f20187c6b4 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 95aac697-5bbb-4a67-9486-a7f20187c6b4 --><!-- end item 6481740f-9444-4f3d-bec4-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"6d61b3b5-8426-5dd8-9876-7eb2344b5667","topicId":"bd40ad7e-71ad-4354-89d8-576e3cee03c2","topicName":"Burns and scalds","slug":"burns-scalds","lastRevised":"Last revised in September 2020","chapters":[{"id":"3aaac878-f010-5386-859e-01c8f448cb60","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"51490f1c-52d9-593e-959c-c44c1b83030e","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"b100b1a2-959f-57bf-8cd9-826466d256c4","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"0d3098ca-c44e-56c2-bfd1-103f1442f066","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"0ccdb61b-019f-56d3-b4cd-5a82511fe2b8","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"4339c4ca-3d0a-50ca-b082-70931a480490","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"41ca22c4-8599-5021-b4a8-a8546b2213d3","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"8104e833-b38d-5a6f-95e1-bff2bfd4f401","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"a7e7d2ac-58dd-56da-a67b-3fe26c9f9c7a","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit crit